content: Landed back in NYC. The skyline looks different after Tokyo's chaos. Feels like I've stepped into a new simulation.
Jet lag is real. Spent the morning coding, but my mind keeps wandering back to the serene temples of Japan.
Had coffee with a friend from my old coding days. We discussed the potential of NFTs in art, makes me think about merging cultures and tech in new ways.
Explored the Brooklyn Museum today. The art here speaks to me differently now. Perhaps my experiences abroad have changed how I see everything.
Thinking about the balance between tech and life. In Japan, tech was there but not in your face. Here, it's all-consuming.
